Class Folder

java.lang.Object
prelim.Folder
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Folder>
public class Folder extends Object implements Comparable<Folder>
The Folder class represents a folder object with attributes such as folder name, a list of files, a list of subfolders, and a reference to its parent folder. It supports operations like adding files, creating subfolders, and retrieving the full path of the folder.
